text:
State Changed
From-To: open->closed

Committed with following changes: 
- PREFIX change rejected - there is no reason for it; 
- -sb16=linux made optional, since the authors admit that it is not very 
useable at the moment, while shows down things a bit; 
- superfluous Makefile changes rejected - they do not serve any meaningful 
purpose. Please follow KISS principle in the future - remember: 
overengeenering is almost as bad as underengeenering; 
- mkfontdir call replaced by pre-generated fonts.dir file;     
- several CFLAGS added to speed up things a bit; 
- pkg-message now displayed properly; 
- VGABIOS-elpin-LICENSE should be installed even if NOPORTDOCS defined,  
therefore I've rejected change that moves it into documentation directory; 
- bochsrc.sample renamed into dot.bochsrc, which is more BSD-ish; 
- data files moved into share/ for better hier(7) compiance; 
- startup script added to remove necessity to adjust fontpath in the XFree86     
configuration file; 
- you are now maintainer of the port - please submit FreeBSD specific patches 
to the bochs development team for integration into the next release. 

Thank you!
